------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A license-aware, independent reimplementation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

wxNotepad++ is an independent, ground-up reimplementation of a Notepad++-style
editor built on wxWidgets + wxStyledTextCtrl (Scintilla) and Lexilla. It is NOT
a fork of, and contains no source code copied from, the Notepad++ application.

Notepad++ is used ONLY as:
  * a functional/behavioral reference (to match look-and-feel and command
    semantics), and
  * a test target (to compare behavior against).

No Notepad++ implementation code is reproduced in this project's own sources
(`src/`); the editor is original work. This mirrors the approach taken by other
clean reimplementations (e.g. DjvuNet relative to DjVuLibre): the reference
implementation informs and validates behavior, it is not a code dependency.

Notepad++ is a trademark of its respective owner. This project is not affiliated
with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Notepad++ or its authors. The UI uses the
wxNotepad++ name throughout; the app icon is the project's own SVG (whose green
plate + monogram echo the upstream styling).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Licensing direction (GPL now, permissive later)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The project is GPL v3 today. Most Notepad++-derived files have already been
replaced or clean-room-reimplemented (icons, command ids, plugin-ABI headers,
themes, the default styler, and three GPL lexers). The committed goal is to drop
the remaining GPL ties and relicense the project permissively — solely to give
users and downstream developers more freedom, with NO commercial agenda. The
reasons we remain on GPL for now (chiefly the legally-unsettled plugin-ABI
reproduction), the progress so far, and the plan to get permissive are in
docs/FUTURE_PLANS.md.

